sentences: He was born on 5 January 1951 in Colombo.
In December 2018, he was hospitalized due to a heart condition.
On 6 December 2018, he underwent a heart surgery at the Durdans hospital.
He died on 12 December 2018 at the age of 67 after the cardiac arrest.
Funeral service was held at 4.00 pm on 15 December 2018 at the Kohuwala Public Cemetery.
His career spanned nearly a decade and a half as the lead guitarist of the popular band Super Star led by Ernest Soysa since 1974.
They were the first band to be invited twice overseas in 1975 to perform in Kuwait and Bahrain.
On 10 December 2006, he staged his own musical show 'Swarna Sarani' at the BMICH.
In 1984, he made playback singing for the comedy film Kakilley Rajjuruwo directed by Tissa Nagodavithana.

On 7 November 2015, The Super Stars Super Concert Musical Extravaganza was held at the Nelum Pokuna theatre, Colombo at 6.30 p.m to mark the reunion of the original members of the band almost after 25 years.
In 2016, he became the music director of the film Weerawarna directed by Shahiru Ranasinghe.
